        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "ci: upgrade actions, add least-privilege permissions and concurrency",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nA few hardening/maintenance upgrades to `.github/workflows/ci.yml`, found while auditing the workflow:\n\n- **`actions/checkout@v4` → `v6`** and **`actions/setup-node@v4` → `v6`** — both were two majors behind. I checked the v6 changelogs: setup-node v6's only breaking change is to *implicit* cache auto-detection defaults for npm/pnpm/yarn — this workflow already sets `cache: pnpm` explicitly, so it's unaffected.\n- **`permissions: contents: read`** — no `permissions` block means the `GITHUB_TOKEN` gets the repo's default permissions (often broader read/write). This workflow only checks out code and runs tests/build, so least-privilege `contents: read` is sufficient.\n- **`concurrency` group with `cancel-in-progress: true`** — rapid pushes to the same branch/PR currently queue up redundant full-matrix runs (2 Node versions × full lint/typecheck/test/build pipeline each). This cancels superseded runs to save CI minutes.\n\nThis is independent of #6 (the Node 20→22/24 bump), so I split it into its own PR to keep changes atomic.\n\n## Hosted workflow run — live proof (this exact modified file, on GitHub-hosted runners)\n\nGitHub gates first-time fork-contributor workflow runs on this PR behind maintainer approval, but `push` also triggers this workflow (`branches: [\"**\"]`) — so the **exact byte-for-byte modified workflow file from this branch** already ran end-to-end on GitHub's hosted infrastructure when I pushed it to my fork:\n\n**Run:** https://github.com/joeVenner/vox/actions/runs/27153484253 (commit `7c8c5723f45e`, the current PR head) — **✅ both matrix jobs succeeded**\n\nCopied live output confirming each change actually took effect at runtime:\n\n**1. `permissions: contents: read` — confirmed narrowed in the live job setup:**\n```\n##[group]GITHUB_TOKEN Permissions\nContents: read\nMetadata: read\n##[endgroup]\n```\n(Default unscoped tokens carry many more scopes — this confirms the block is respected by the runner.)\n\n**2. `actions/checkout@v6` — ran and checked out the PR head commit cleanly:**\n```\n##[group]Run actions/checkout@v6\nwith:\n  repository: joeVenner/vox\n  ...\nSyncing repository: joeVenner/vox\n[command]/usr/bin/git -c protocol.version=2 fetch --no-tags --prune --no-recurse-submodules --depth=1 origin +7c8c5723f45eb5d68441f6c6c953361b523f770d:refs/remotes/origin/chore/upgrade-ci-actions\n```\n\n**3. `actions/setup-node@v6` — resolved and cached Node correctly:**\n```\n##[group]Run actions/setup-node@v6\nwith:\n  node-version: 22\nFound in cache @ /opt/hostedtoolcache/node/22.22.3/x64\n[warning]This project is configured to use pnpm because /home/runner/work/vox/vox/package.json has a \"packageManager\" field\n```\n\n**4. Full pipeline green on the live runner (identical to what `main`'s CI runs):**\n```\n> pnpm run lint\n> pnpm run format:check && oxlint --deny-warnings src test\nAll matched files use the correct format.\nFinished in 182ms on 23 files using 4 threads.\nFound 0 warnings and 0 errors.\nFinished in 11ms on 18 files with 95 rules using 4 threads.\n\n> pnpm run typecheck\n> tsgo -p tsconfig.json --noEmit\n(clean exit)\n\n> pnpm test\n# tests 16\n# pass 16\n# fail 0\n\n> pnpm run build\nESM dist/cli.js     30.46 KB\n⚡️ Build success\n```\nJob conclusion: `Complete job` → success, both `test (20)` and `test (22)` matrix legs green.\n\n## Local proof (supplementary — confirms the underlying pipeline this workflow invokes is unaffected)\n\n```\n$ python3 -c \"import yaml; d = yaml.safe_load(open('.github/workflows/ci.yml')); ...\"\nYAML parses OK\npermissions: {'contents': 'read'}\nconcurrency: {'group': '${{ github.workflow }}-${{ github.ref }}', 'cancel-in-progress': True}\ncheckout: ['actions/checkout@v6']\nsetup-node: ['actions/setup-node@v6']\n\n$ gh api repos/actions/checkout/git/refs/tags/v6 --jq '.ref'\nrefs/tags/v6\n$ gh api repos/actions/setup-node/git/refs/tags/v6 --jq '.ref'\nrefs/tags/v6\n\n$ pnpm exec oxlint --deny-warnings src test && pnpm run typecheck && pnpm test && pnpm run build\nFound 0 warnings and 0 errors.\n# tests 16 / # pass 16 / # fail 0\nESM dist/cli.js  ⚡️ Build success\n```\n(Run on Node v22.22.3, matching the PR head commit `7c8c5723f45e`.)\n\nNote on the matrix shown in the linked run (`[20, 22]`): this branch was cut from `main` before #6 landed, so it still carries the pre-bump matrix — irrelevant to what's being verified here (the action versions, permissions, and concurrency config), which are matrix-independent and identical to what would run post-merge.\n",
