        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(ui): prevent skill toggle state transfer with Lit repeat directive [AI-assisted]",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- **Problem**: When a skill toggle is flipped in the Skills view (e.g., from \"Ready\" tab), the toggled skill moves to a different status tab. The checkbox checked state bleeds into the next skill that takes its place. Issue #89661.\n- **Root Cause**: The skills list is rendered using Array.map() without stable DOM keys. When a skill moves to another group/visibility after toggle, Lit reuses the DOM element for the next skill. The checkbox .checked binding retains its previous value.\n- **Fix**: Replace Array.map() with Lit s repeat() directive keyed by group.id and skill.skillKey to ensure stable DOM identity across re-renders.\n- **What changed**: ui/src/ui/views/skills.ts — imported repeat from lit/directives/repeat.js; replaced 2 Array.map() calls with repeat(). ui/src/ui/views/skills.test.ts — added regression test verifying checkbox state preservation across status tab transitions.\n- **What did NOT change**: No behavioral or visual changes. Skill toggle functionality, status tabs, group rendering layout remain identical.\n\n## Verification\n\n- skills.test.ts: 5/5 tests pass (including new regression test)\n- oxfmt --check passes\n- Real browser rendering verified via Playwright headless Chromium\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior addressed**: Skill checkbox toggle state incorrectly transfers to the next skill when a toggled skill moves between status tabs (Ready to Disabled).\n- **Real environment tested**: Windows 10 Pro, Node v24.16.0, Playwright Chromium 148, Vite dev server rendering the actual Skills UI component\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch**: pnpm exec vitest run ui/src/ui/views/skills.test.ts --reporter=verbose\n- **Evidence after fix**: \n\n![Skills UI - All tab](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/425072024/openclaw/fix/skill-toggle-state-transfer-89661/skills-all-tab.png)\n\n*Above: Control UI Skills page rendered with the repeat() fix. 3 skills shown across Workspace and Installed groups. Checkboxes correctly reflect each skill s disabled state independently — GitHub Assistant enabled (checked), Code Reviewer disabled (unchecked), Deploy Helper enabled (checked). No state bleeding between rows.*\n\nTest output: 5 tests passed (1 new regression test), 0 failures. oxfmt --check clean.\n- **Observed result after fix**: The repeat() directive with stable skill.skillKey keys prevents Lit from reusing DOM elements. Each skill s checkbox state is independently bound to its skill.disabled data, not DOM position.\n- **What was not tested**: Full gateway-connected live deployment (no running openclaw gateway in this environment). The Playwright screenshot uses the actual Skills component rendered via Vite dev server with the repeat() fix applied.\n\nFixes #89661",
